sp;</o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><font size=3 color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\nstyle='font-size:12.0pt;color:navy'>The by-product can be used for everything\nfrom watering the grounds, laundry, flushing toilets, etc, etc.\u00a0 The system has\nbeen around for 15 years but it was not until recently, I talked them into\ngoing &#8220;Marine&#8221;.\u00a0 We are now selling them like crazy for Cruise\nShips, yachts, etc, since the &#8220;Green&#8221; movement is growing.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><font size=3 color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\nstyle='font-size:12.0pt;color:navy'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><font size=3 color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\nstyle='font-size:12.0pt;color:navy'>In the water sample photo you can see the\nquality of water on the left that is presently being pumped overboard from\nyachts like Limitless.\u00a0 The bottle in the middle of the photo shows what we do\nwith that.\u00a0 The one on the right is our final stage which exceeds all water\nstandards for marine discharge now, the new 2010 regulations and even the\nfuture.\u00a0 FYI &#8211; the system on Limitless will be illegal in 1 \u00bd years when\nthe new regulations are in effect, as will all other Type II MSD (Marine\nSanitation Devices) units.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><font size=3 color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\nstyle='font-size:12.0pt;color:navy'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><font size=3 color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\nstyle='font-size:12.0pt;color:navy'>We are also having these systems approved\nas individual Sewage Treatment Plants for homes and developments since they\nexceed State regulations for not only re-use, but with one additional step, we\nare exceeding the drinkable water standards for <st1:State w:st=\"on\"><st1:place\n w:st=\"on\">Florida</st1:place></st1:State>. This state, and <st1:State w:st=\"on\"><st1:place\n w:st=\"on\">California</st1:place></st1:State> have the highest standards of the\ncountry.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><font size=3 color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\nstyle='font-size:12.0pt;color:navy'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><font size=3 color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\nstyle='font-size:12.0pt;color:navy'>Check it out at <a\nhref=\"http://www.dragonflymarine.com/\">www.DragonflyMarine.com</a>. \u00a0We are\nstill developing the site but you can see the Beta display.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><font size=3 color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\nstyle='font-size:12.0pt;color:navy'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><font size=3 color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\nstyle='font-size:12.0pt;color:navy'>Kindest regards,<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><font size=3 color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\nstyle='font-size:12.0pt;color:navy'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><font size=5 color=navy face=\"Blackadder ITC\"><span\nstyle='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:\"Blackadder ITC\";color:navy'>Craig Tafoya<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><st1:Street w:st=\"on\"><st1:address w:st=\"on\"><font size=2\n  color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;color:navy'>3778\n  SW 30<sup>th</sup> Ave</span></font></st1:address></st1:Street><font size=2\ncolor=navy><span style='font-size:10.0pt;color:navy'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:City w:st=\"on\"><font size=2\n  color=navy face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;color:navy'>Ft.\n  Lauderdale</span></font></st1:City></st1:place><font size=2 color=navy><span\nstyle='font-size:10.0pt;color:navy'>, <st1:State w:st=\"on\">FL</st1:State> <st1:PostalCode\nw:st=\"on\">33312</st1:PostalCode><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><